            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>yakitori sauce</strong> to a pot over a medium heat and cook for 5 min or until it becomes thick and sticky – this is your <strong>sticky yakitori sauce</strong></p><p>Tip: Watch the sauce like a hawk to make sure it doesn't burn!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2136Step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2136Step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2136Step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2136Step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2136Step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken has had 10-12 min, remove the tray[s] from the oven and brush the <strong>sticky yakitori sauce</strong> all over the skewers</p><p>Drizzle the <strong>remaining honey</strong> and<strong> black sesame seeds</strong> over the <strong>roasted sweet potato </strong>– this is your <strong>candied sweet potato</strong></p><p>Return the trays to the oven for 8 min further or until they are both caramelised and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2136Step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2136Step-7-x400.jpg",
